===== types of alarms =====
1. metric alarm :- Triggers when one metric crosses a threshold.
   Examples:
CPUUtilization > 80%
mem_used_percent > 60%
disk_used_percent > 70%

2. anomaly detection :- Uses machine learning to create a model of expected values and triggers when values deviate from the model.
Examples:
CPU alarm AND Memory alarm
Disk alarm OR StatusCheckFailed alarm

3. composite alarms :- Combines multiple alarms into one.
Examples:
Sudden CPU spike
Unexpected drop in traffic

===== alaram states =====
1. OK :- The metric is within the defined threshold.
2. ALARM :- The metric has crossed the defined threshold.
3. INSUFFICIENT_DATA :- There is not enough data to determine the state of the alarm.

======= download the logs ========
Export CloudWatch Logs to S3 (Console)
Go to AWS Console → CloudWatch → Logs → Log groups

Example: /aws/ec2/mem-disk-logs
Select the Log Group you want to export
Click Actions → Export data to Amazon S3
 Fill in details:
 Time range (From → To)
 Destination S3 bucket (must exist)
 Prefix (optional folder in S3, e.g., ec2-logs/)
Click Export
After export completes, go to S3 → your bucket → download the logs.


