=============== save container logs to aws cloudwatch ==================
1. create a iam user with programmatic access and attach the policy "CloudWatchAgentServerPolicy" to the user.
2. create access key for the user and note down the access key id and secret access key
3. install aws cli on the server where the container is running
4. configure aws cli with the access key id and secret access key
aws configure
5. create a cloudwatch log group

6. now edit the docker compose file to add the following lines to the container for which you want to save logs to cloudwatch
logging:
   driver: awslogs
   options:
     awslogs-group: your-log-group-name
     awslogs-region: your-region
     awslogs-stream: your-stream-prefix
7. now run docker compose up -d
8. now the logs of the container will be saved to cloudwatch log group
9. to view the logs go to cloudwatch -> logs -> log groups -> select your log group -> log streams -> select your log stream -> view the logs

# now export the logs to s3
go to cloudwatch -> logs -> log groups -> select your log group -> actions -> export data to amazon s3 -> fill in the details -> export

